[2] Norovirus, confirmed - hospital Ireland (Sligo)
Date: Tue 7 Feb 2006
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Ocean fm Radio News, Ireland, 7 Feb 2006 [edited]
<http://www.oceanfm.ie/onair/sligoleitrimnews.php?articleid=000002545>

Ireland: Outbreak of Winter Vomiting Bug at St. John's Hospital in Sligo
-----------------------------------------------
An outbreak of the winter vomiting bug [norovirus infection] has been
confirmed at St. John's Hospital in Sligo. The HSE have confirmed
this evening they are dealing with an outbreak of the virus at the
hospital. They say they have put in place precautions to control the
spread of it and that these are working satisfactorily.
However, the HSE have requested the cooperation of the public in
restricting their visiting to essential visiting only, particularly
at the weekend. Visitors are requested to visit one patient only and
not to move around the hospital.
